<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f96654572631716>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Wizard kiting</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 4:55 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=392><span id= >Durnhelm</span></a><br><span id=notbold>14 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;     Wizards are quite fun. You start out slow, but pick it up after 30 or so. We are exceptional kiters after we Bonds of Force(if you dont believe me, try it) Actually, many Wizards I know have got up through the 50s by just soloing from 34 or so onward. Only problem is you need SoW to kite well, or the Journyman boots. Ive found some good places to kite in Kunark. Namely the Mountain Giant fort in The Frontier Mountains and The Overthere. Those are good from the low 30s on up till the low 40s. Many Wizards I have talked to like to kite spectres as well, although I never really took a liking to it. Hill Giants on the other hand are more my speed...although I wouldnt suggest trying a Hill Giant until at least 39. 1 thing to remember when kiting is to always watch out for people, as it is very rude behavior to kite a mob into a group. Hill Giants or Sand giants will do good in the 40s, as well as some of the higher mobs in The Overthere. Dreadlands also present a whole slough of possible targets, a favorite for many is right outside Karnors. Be careful if you must zone though, as a constant trainbringer is very frowned upon. Sea Fury Cyclops in the Ocean of Tears is a good idea in the high 40s(48+) and after you get Conflageration and Ice Comet at 44 and 49, respectively, it makes your job much easier. I havent had much exp kiting after 51:) Namely because I havent made it their yet, but Im sure I will find something to kill. I hope I helped someone out with this...some Wizard out their thats stuck grouping somewhere and wants a change of pace, any questions look me up on Povar or email me. Later.<br><br>       </p>&nbsp;<br>Durnhelm Eorling <br>"All that is gold does not glitter"<br>57 Wizard,<br></td></tr>
