	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=11&mid=96665452817214>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=11&mid=96665452817214>How to battle using a Wizard</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=11&mid=96665452817214#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 11:08 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=475><span id= >Artannis</span></a><br><span id=notbold>5 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Wizard's are of course the master nukers.&nbsp;&nbsp;But that does not mean that they are better than any of the other caster classes.  Each have their own specialties.  But when it comes to doing mass amounts of damage in a short time.  Wizard's are the masters!<br><br>The best way to battle using a wizard is in a group.  You can of course battle alone, but at lower levels it's really annoying when you're trying to cast spells.  <br>"You begin casting."<br>"You are hit for 26 points of damage."<br>"Your casting is interrupted."<br>It goes on like that.  Anyways, it is true that Wizards are of the most use in higher levels, but that doesn't mean that you have to be bored in the lower levels.<br><br>Now,  find a group, (try to find a balanced one with at least one healer.  It'll make your job a lot easier).  During battle, don't nuke away with every point of mana that you have.  Sit and watch.  I'm not saying don't participate, and steal free exp, but wait for when it looks like you are really needed.  You can stand back, because you don't have to be touching a MOB to cast your spells on them.  When it looks like a MOB is going to run away.  NUKE IT!!!  If you let it go, it's probably going to bring back another huge train to fight your already wearied battle group. Should it ever happen, and your group has been very weakened, that's probably your cue to teleport you, and your group out.  Keep an eye on all your teamates health bars, if one gets too low, lend a hand and use some mana, or alert the group healer.  It's no good to have the party die one by one.  And of course if your party ever does bite off more than it can kill, again it is your cue to teleport out.  Your group can heal and then go back for more later.<br><br>Another important point while battling, is to be very careful with your area effect spells.  They can be useful, but they can also have all the dungeon's MOBs gang beating you.  A wizard is NOT meant to take that kind of punishment.  If you do get a ew enemies chasing around, alert some of your group's tanks.  Have them come and deal with it.  Don't run around in circles with the MOBs chasing you and the tanks chasing them.  Go to your tanks, and have them get them off you, and if you're almost dead, alert the healer, after all, that's what they're there for.  You do your job and let them do theirs.<br><br>One last thing I want to mention is that, if your group is killing lower level enemies, or only a few at a time, why not jump in with your staff.  It's another way to raise that one hand blunt.  Well, that's my opinion, I hope you all find it useful.<br><br>Artannis<br>High Elven<br>Wizard<br>Tunare Server</p>&nbsp;<br>"People will belive any lie either because they want it to be true, or they're arfaid it's true."<br></td></tr>
